        "client_msg_id": "4574f800-7afc-41d5-8da5-375763404953",
        "text": "I truly dislike the Slack UX for our FoC use-case. Currently the onus is on the first responder to remember to hit the \"reply to thread\" button, because no \"reply\" button appears below a top-level post until the first reply has been issued. Maybe the protocol should be that a top-level poster must immediately reply to their own thread, even if with an empty reply (\"-\")?",
